com.tsgrp.migration

Class MigrationPipeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.MigrationPipeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.Aware, org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware

    public class MigrationPipeline
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.springframework.context.ApplicationContextAware
    The pipeline that connects a source to a target and invokes all Source, Map and Target Migration Threads.

      • setOptimizeThreadCountBasedOnQueueSize

        public void setOptimizeThreadCountBasedOnQueueSize(boolean optimizeThreadCountBasedOnQueueSize)
        injected, boolean to determine if thread count should be optimized based on queue size. When TRUE, if the queue size is less than the number of source, mapping, or target threads (the case of a very small migration), then only then the thread size will be reduced to 1 source, 1 mapping, and 1 target thread. This avoids starting a bunch of threads that won't be used and could cause race conditions.
        Parameters:
        optimizeThreadCountBasedOnQueueSize -

      • setShutdownHook

        public void setShutdownHook(java.lang.Thread value)
        The shutdown hook is set and registered during #startEngine so that an orderly shutdown can occur when interrupted. After a normal shutdown, it is unregistered so that shutdown logic is not invoked twice. Only injected by command-line apps, not useful in web application.

      • setPopulateQueueAsync

        public void setPopulateQueueAsync(boolean value)
        Injected (optional). If true, will start a thread to populate the queue asynchronously. For async mode, configure optimizeThreadCountBasedOnQueueSize to false as thread count optimization is not supported.
        Parameters:
        {boolean} - - defaults to false.

      • shutdown

        public void shutdown()
        Shutdown all active source, map and target threads; then mark any active queue items as Aborted; and close the Migration Log. Called normally from ; from engage() when an error occurs; and from MigrationEngine's ShutdownHook.

      • asyncQueuePopulationStarted

        public void asyncQueuePopulationStarted()
        Set a flag to indicate the queue populator is running to ensure the @SourceMigrationThread does not shut down the migration before all items are added to the queue.

      • asyncQueuePopulationFinished

        public void asyncQueuePopulationFinished()
        Queue population has finished - flip the flag so we can break out of the loop in SourceMigrationThread.process() If there are no items in the queue, this will stop the loop in engage() and trigger disengagement. In addition, set the queue population time for the tracker.

      • getStatus

        public java.util.Properties getStatus(java.lang.String pipelinePrefix,
                                      java.lang.String itemPrefix)
        Returns a java.util.Properties object containing information about this pipeline. This method is called in the servlet for the UI so that the user can see a status of the pipeline and migration.
        Parameters:

        itemPrefix - String to start each item status property with; omitted if null or blank.
